Pseudocode:

1. Loop from 1 to 100 (both inclusive)
2. If the loop index is divisible evenly by 3 and 5, print 'FizzBuzz'
3. Else if the loop index is divisible evenly by only 3, print 'Fizz'
4. Else if the loop index is divisible evenly by only 5, print 'Buzz'
5. Else, just print the loop index
6. End Loop

Code:

```javascript
for(let i = 1; i <= 100; i++) {
    if(i % 15 === 0) {
        console.log('FizzBuzz');
    } else if(i % 3 === 0) {
        console.log('Fizz');
    } else if(i % 5 === 0) {
        console.log('Buzz');
    } else {
        console.log(i);
    }
}
```

